    </equation><para id="import-auto-id949808"><emphasis>Solution for (b)</emphasis> </para>
    <para id="import-auto-id2821869">Again <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">−</m:mo></m:mrow><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mtext>ΔPE</m:mtext><m:mrow><m:mtext>g</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:msub><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mi/></m:mrow><m:mtext>ΔKE</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{ - Δ"PE" rSub { size 8{g} } =Δ"KE"} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math>. In this case there is initial kinetic energy, so <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi/><m:mrow><m:mtext>ΔKE</m:mtext><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:mfrac></m:mrow><m:mrow>
<m:mi>m</m:mi>
